'''越南長襖'''（{{vie|v=áo dài|hn=襖𨱾}}），常音譯為'''奧黛'''，为近現代[[京族|京族]]的服装。起源于18世纪[[顺化|顺化]][[广南国|广南国]]的宫廷服装，越南长袄于19世纪和20世纪初演变成五身[[贵族|贵族]]长袍。受巴黎时装启发，阮吉祥和其他艺术家于20世纪20年代到30年代联合印度支那大學（今[[河内國家大學|河内國家大學]])重新设计了五身长袍作为现代服饰<ref name="Ellis">{{cite web|last=Ellis |first=Claire |title=Ao Dai: The National Costume |newspaper=Things Asian |year=1996 |url=http://www.thingsasian.com/stories-photos/1083 |accessdate=2008-08-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705105011/http://www.thingsasian.com/stories-photos/1083 |archivedate=2008-07-05 }}
</ref>。改版款式被艺术家和[[自力文团|自力文团]]推崇为现代国服。50年代，[[胡志明市|西贡]]设计师将服装收紧，制造出现在{{le|越南女性|Women in Vietnam}}穿着的版本<ref name="Ellis">{{cite web|last=Ellis |first=Claire |title=Ao Dai: The National Costume |newspaper=Things Asian |year=1996 |url=http://www.thingsasian.com/stories-photos/1083 |accessdate=2008-08-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705105011/http://www.thingsasian.com/stories-photos/1083 |archivedate=2008-07-05 }}
</ref>。60年代70年代初，这件服装在[[越南共和国|越南共和国]]十分流行。过[[越南新年|新年]]或出席其他场合，越南男子会穿着由厚织物制造的{{le|越南织锦长袍|Áo gấm|织锦长袍}}。

学界认为，越南长袄强调女性美和越南民族主义的结合，尤其是在越南和海外[[越侨|越侨]]之間十分兴盛的“长袄小姐”选美<ref name="Lieu">{{Cite journal | last = Lieu | first = Nhi T. | title = Remembering "the Nation" through pageantry: femininity and the politics of Vietnamese womanhood in the "Hoa Hau Ao Dai" contest | journal = [[Frontiers:_A_Journal_of_Women's_Studies|Frontiers: A Journal of Women's Studies]] | volume = 21 | issue = 1-2 | pages = 127–151 | publisher = University of Nebraska Press via JSTOR | doi = 10.2307/3347038 | date = 2000 | url = https://dx.doi.org/10.2307/3347038 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref>。越南长袄是英文字典中为数不多的越南语词汇之一。

== 历史 ==
=== 前阮朝 ===
数世纪以来，农妇们通常会以[[肚兜|肚兜]]打底，外穿衬衫或大衣，外加短裙<ref name="Leshkowich89">Leshkowich, p. 89.</ref>。另一方面，贵族则青睐仿造[[汉服|汉服]]、[[韩服|韩服]]和[[和服|和服]]的{{le|交领衣|Áo giao lĩnh}}<ref name="THUYVU">{{cite web | last = Vu | first = Thuy | title = Đi tìm ngàn năm áo mũ | newspaper = Tuoi Tre | year = 2014 | url = http://tuoitre.vn/tin/chinh-tri-xa-hoi/phong-su-ky-su/20141007/di-tim-ngan-nam-ao-mu/654967.html | accessdate = 2015-06-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150617124135/http://tuoitre.vn/tin/chinh-tri-xa-hoi/phong-su-ky-su/20141007/di-tim-ngan-nam-ao-mu/654967.html | archive-date = 2015-06-17 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref name="TVAN">{{cite web | last = Unknown | first = T.Van | title = Ancient costumes of Vietnamese people | newspaper = Vietnamnet | year = 2013 | url = http://english.vietnamnet.vn/fms/vietnam-in-photos/78314/ancient-costumes-of-vietnam.html | accessdate = 2015-06-16 | archive-date = 2015-06-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150617082002/http://english.vietnamnet.vn/fms/vietnam-in-photos/78314/ancient-costumes-of-vietnam.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。1744年，[[顺化市|顺化]]君主[[阮福阔|阮福阔]]下令宫中男女都要穿长裤和前面有纽扣的长衫<ref name="Ellis" />。文人[[黎贵惇|黎贵惇]]把这套新奇的衣服唤作áo dài。而南方宫廷人员与河内[[郑主|郑主]]的朝臣不同，穿裙摆很长的{{le|交领衣|áo giao lĩnh}}<ref name="THUYVU" />。

中国[[明代|明代]]的服装风格影响了[[阮朝|阮朝]]的越南人<ref name="Woodside1971 3">{{cite book|author=Alexander Woodside|title=Vietnam and the Chinese Model: A Comparative Study of Vietnamese and Chinese Government in the First Half of the Nineteenth Century|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0LgSI9UQNpwC&pg=PA134&dq=vietnamese+skirt+trousers+tunics#v=onepage&q=vietnamese%20skirt%20trousers%20tunics&f=false|year=1971|publisher=Harvard Univ Asia Center|isbn=978-0-674-93721-5|pages=134–|access-date=2017-12-08|archive-date=2017-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226215359/https://books.google.com/books?id=0LgSI9UQNpwC&pg=PA134&dq=vietnamese+skirt+trousers+tunics#v=onepage&q=vietnamese%20skirt%20trousers%20tunics&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Globalization: A View by Vietnamese Consumers Through Wedding Windows |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4bmbP5Pg5jAC&pg=PA34&dq=vietnamese+skirt+trousers+tunics#v=onepage&q=vietnamese%20skirt%20trousers%20tunics&f=false |year=2008 |publisher=ProQuest |isbn=978-0-549-68091-8 |pages=34– |access-date=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2017-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226215454/https://books.google.com/books?id=4bmbP5Pg5jAC&pg=PA34&dq=vietnamese+skirt+trousers+tunics#v=onepage&q=vietnamese%20skirt%20trousers%20tunics&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://angelasancartier.net/ao-dai-vietnams-national-dress |title=Ao dai – Vietnam’s national dress - Clothing and Fashion<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2016-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121182241/http://angelasancartier.net/ao-dai-vietnams-national-dress |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://beyondvictoriana.com/2010/03/14/beyond-victoriana-18-transcultural-tradition-of-the-vietnamese-ao-dai/ |title=#18 Transcultural Tradition of the Vietnamese Ao Dai {{!}} Beyond Victoriana<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2010-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323122205/http://beyondvictoriana.com/2010/03/14/beyond-victoriana-18-transcultural-tradition-of-the-vietnamese-ao-dai/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://fashion-history.lovetoknow.com/clothing-types-styles/ao-dai |title=Ao Dai {{!}} LoveToKnow<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2016-02-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204032753/http://fashion-history.lovetoknow.com/clothing-types-styles/ao-dai |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tor.com/2010/10/20/ao-dai-and-i-steampunk-essay/ |title=The Ao Dai and I: A Personal Essay on Cultural Identity and Steampunk {{!}} Tor.com<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2016-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307004314/http://www.tor.com/2010/10/20/ao-dai-and-i-steampunk-essay/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他们开始穿明清时期汉族的长袍和裤子。20世纪20年代的越南长袄又在原有的中国款式上加入了贴身且紧凑的褶裥<ref name="Reid2015">{{cite book|author=Anthony Reid|title=A History of Southeast Asia: Critical Crossroads|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cETJBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA285&dq=vietnamese+skirt+trousers+tunics#v=onepage&q=vietnamese%20skirt%20trousers%20tunics&f=false|date=2015-06-02|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-0-631-17961-0|pages=285–|access-date=2017-12-08|archive-date=2017-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226215531/https://books.google.com/books?id=cETJBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA285&dq=vietnamese+skirt+trousers+tunics#v=onepage&q=vietnamese%20skirt%20trousers%20tunics&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。阮朝政府强制推行中国式的裤子和长袍。直到那时，越南北部与世隔绝的小村庄的村民穿裙子<ref name="Rambo2005">{{cite book|author=A. Terry Rambo|title=Searching for Vietnam: Selected Writings on Vietnamese Culture and Society|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ippuAAAAMAAJ&q=In+their+place,+the+court+demanded+the+use+of+tunic+and+trousers+copied+from+the+then+current+fashion+in+the+Chinese+court.+...+the+wearing+of+skirts+their+use+continued+in+remote+villages+in+the+Northern+part+of+Vietnam+until+the+1920s.1+In+the+less+...&dq=In+their+place,+the+court+demanded+the+use+of+tunic+and+trousers+copied+from+the+then+current+fashion+in+the+Chinese+court.+...+the+wearing+of+skirts+their+use+continued+in+remote+villages+in+the+Northern+part+of+Vietnam+until+the+1920s.1+In+the+less+...&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjDt9uK7LrNAhWIQyYKHdNIDj0Q6AEIHjAA|year=2005|publisher=Kyoto University Press|isbn=978-1-920901-05-9|page=64}}</ref>。中国明朝、唐朝和汉朝的服饰被阮福阔的军人和官吏采纳<ref name="WernerWhitmore2012">{{cite book|author1=Jayne Werner|author2=John K. Whitmore|author3=George Dutton|title=Sources of Vietnamese Tradition|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZHD4Asj0FagC&pg=PA295&dq=vietnamese+skirt+trousers+tunics&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiV2LO26brNAhWPZiYKHcUuDwYQ6AEINjAA#v=onepage&q=vietnamese%20skirt%20trousers%20tunics&f=false|date=2012-08-21|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=978-0-231-51110-0|pages=295–}}</ref>。中国服饰到[[黎朝|黎朝]]开始影响越南人的服装。现在的长袄由阮朝领主引入<ref>http://english.vietnamnet.vn/fms/special-reports/151794/vietnamese-ao-dai--from-dong-son-bronze-drum-to-int-l-beauty-contests.html {{Wayback|url=http://english.vietnamnet.vn/fms/special-reports/151794/vietnamese-ao-dai--from-dong-son-bronze-drum-to-int-l-beauty-contests.html |date=20171127140303 }} https://www.vietnambreakingnews.com/2016/02/vietnamese-ao-dai-from-dong-son-bronze-drum-to-intl-beauty-contests/ {{Wayback|url=https://www.vietnambreakingnews.com/2016/02/vietnamese-ao-dai-from-dong-son-bronze-drum-to-intl-beauty-contests/ |date=20160806030945 }}</ref>。

=== 19世纪 ===
五身袄双摆在前面和后面缝合，主前摆下面又藏着“小摆”。双摆在两侧开衩，这点在后期的长袄中得到保留。相较于现代长袄，它的前后摆更宽更松更短。领子比较高，有纽扣，类似于现代长袄。女性穿衣服时不扣纽，会露出打底的[[肚兜|肚兜]]。

=== 20世纪 ===
[[File:VN_Phat_Diem_tango7174.jpg|thumb]]穿长袄的聖母雕像。]]
1917年开始办学的[[顺化|顺化]]同庆（Đồng Khánh）高中极力推崇长袄作为学生校服<ref name="kauffner">{{cite web|last1=Kauffner|first1=Peter|title=Ao dai: The allure and grace of Vietnam's traditional dress|url=https://visions-of-indochina.com/latestnews/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ao-dai-article.pdf|website=Asia Insights: Destination Asia|accessdate=2017-12-08|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130522194437/http://visions-of-indochina.com/latestnews/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/ao-dai-article.pdf|archivedate=2013-05-22}}</ref>。首件现代长袄于1921年在巴黎时装展亮相。1930年，化名黎穆（Le Mur）的河内艺术家吉祥（Cát Tường）受五身袄和巴黎时装启发设计了一件服装，这件衣服前后摆扫地，利用缝褶和内收的腰部贴合身体曲线<ref name="Leshkowich91">Leshkowich p. 91.</ref>。织物变得便宜，使用多层布料和加厚前后摆的原理不再有。现代纺织品制造允许用更宽的裙摆，无需将窄的裙摆缝在一起。1935年1月，模特儿阮氏候（Nguyễn Thị Hậu）穿着雷穆的长袄（或称“时髦”长袄）的照片刊登在《今日报》，引起一时轰动<ref name="ninh">{{cite web|title=A Fashion Revolution |newspaper=Ninh Thuận P&T |url=http://www.ninhthuanpt.com.vn/english/Fashion1/index.htm |accessdate=2008-08-02 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080623224038/http://www.ninhthuanpt.com.vn/English/Fashion1/index.htm |archivedate=2008-06-23 }}</ref>。这种款式得到自力文团艺术家的推崇，成为现代的国服<ref name="aodai4">{{cite web | title = Vietnamese Ao dai history | newspaper = Aodai4u | url = http://www.aodai4u.com/aboutaodai.html | accessdate = 2008-08-02 | archive-date = 2008-08-19 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080819145415/http://www.aodai4u.com/aboutaodai.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。画家黎铺（Lê Phô）于1934年起引进多种长袄流行款式。[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]期间，这种西化服装暂时消失。

20世纪50年代，西贡设计师收紧长袄，创造了如今常见的款式<ref name="Ellis"/>。铁立（Thiết Lập）裁缝店的陈金（Trần Kim）和勇（Dũng）裁缝店创造了{{le|插肩袖|Raglan sleeve}}且衣领至腋下对角缝的衣服<ref name="Ellis"/>。越南共和国第一夫人[[陈丽春|陈丽春]]从1958年起推广无领版本。1960年到1975年，长袄最受欢迎<ref name="Elmore">{{cite news |last=Elmore |first=Mick |title=Ao Dai Enjoys A Renaissance Among Women : In Vietnam, A Return to Femininity |work=International New York Times |date=1997-09-17 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/09/17/news/17iht-saodai.t.html |accessdate=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305235430/http://www.nytimes.com/1997/09/17/news/17iht-saodai.t.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1968年，色彩鲜艳的嬉皮士版长袄亮相。这款迷你版长袄实现便利，开缝延至腰部，裙摆只及膝盖<ref name="Leshkowich91" />。

相较于北部，长袄在南部更普及。1954年和1975年分别掌管北越和南越的共产党对长袄爱恨交织。他们称赞它是国服，[[越南南方民族解放陣線|越南南方民族解放陣線]]谈判代表[[阮氏萍|阮氏萍]]出席[[巴黎和平协约|巴黎和会]]时便曾穿长袄<ref name="Overland" />。而西化版于60年代到70年代因和“腐朽的”西贡有关遭到谴责<ref name="Leshkowich92">Leshkowich p. 92.</ref>。80年代，经济危机、饥荒和与[[柬越战争|柬埔寨交战]]堆叠起来，成为时装的发展低谷<ref name="Valverde">{{cite web | last = Valverde | first = Caroline Kieu | title = The History and Revival of the Vietnamese ''Ao Dai'' | newspaper = NHA magazine | year = 2006 | url = http://www.nhamagazine.com/back_issue/issue_0506/ac_p1.shtml | accessdate = 2008-08-02 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080704053408/http://www.nhamagazine.com/back_issue/issue_0506/ac_p1.shtml | archivedate = 2008-07-04  }}</ref>。除了婚礼及其他正式场合，很少有人穿长袄，而旧式的宽松风格更讨人喜欢<ref name="Leshkowich92"/>。同时，海外越侨则保持在[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]][[长滩|长滩]]举行“越南长袄小姐”（Hoa Hậu Áo Dài）选美的传统<ref name="Ellis"/>。

80年代末，长袄复兴，时值国有企业和学校开始将之作为制服<ref name="Ellis"/>。1989年，1.6万人出席了在[[胡志明市|胡志明市]]举办的长袄小姐选美比赛<ref>{{Cite web | last1 = Vu | first1 = Lan | title = Ao Dai Viet Nam | newspaper = Viettouch | year = 2002 | url = http://www.viettouch.com/aodai/aodai-changes.htm | accessdate = 2008-07-03 | archive-date = 2008-09-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080906113243/http://www.viettouch.com/aodai/aodai-changes.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。1995年，穿着长袄的常琼梅（Trường Quỳnh Mai）在东京的国际小姐选美上获得“最佳国服”奖时，《新时尚》（Thời Trang Trẻ）再度将其加冕为越南的“国家灵魂”<ref name="Leshkowich79">Leshkowich p. 79.</ref>。随后的“长袄狂潮”持续了好几年，使得更多人将这件服装当作校服<ref name="Leshkowich97">Leshkowich p. 97.</ref>。

== 现状 ==
[[File:Ao-dai-xu-Hue-2.jpg|thumbnail]]
越南政府支持现代长袄设计，不再将之视为政治争议<ref name="Valverde"/>。一般谈到越南长袄，就会联系到爱国主义情怀。越南名人黎仕煌（Le Si Hoang）在西贡开长袄服装店，供慕名前来的人们探访<ref name="Valverde"/>。游客们到河内，在梁文干（Loung Van Can）街可以找到长袄<ref>{{cite news|title=Traditional ''ao dai'' grace foreign bodies |url=http://vietnamnews.vnagency.com.vn/2004-12/18/Stories/33.htm |work=VNS |date=2004-12-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041224075607/http://vietnamnews.vnagency.com.vn/2004-12/18/Stories/33.htm |archivedate=2004-12-24 |accessdate=2016-08-24}}</ref>。中部地区的高雅城市[[顺化市|顺化市]]以长袄、斗笠和穿着体面的女性闻名。

长袄现今是婚礼、[[越南新年|新年]]庆祝及其他正式场合的正式服裝。南部普通中学的女教师（主要是高中以下）和女学生将长袄作为制服，教师制服没有要求颜色和图案，而学生的[[校服|校服]]采用纯白色和花朵等小图案。企业一般要求女员工穿制服，其中就有长袄，所以[[空中乘务员|空中服務員]]、[[接待员|接待员]]、银行职员、餐馆工作人员和酒店工作人员都会穿长袄。

[[File:Ao_dai_le_hoi.JPG|thumbnail]]
最流行的长袄款式的上[[躯干|身]]收得很紧，突出胸部和曲线。衣服尽管包住整个身体，却有挑逗性，尤其是薄布料制作的。有一个说法：“长袄覆盖了一切，但什么都不隐藏”<ref name="Overland">{{cite web |url = http://www.overlandclub.jp/en/info/vn_aodai.html |title = Vietnamese AoDai |work=Overlandclub |accessdate = 2008-07-02 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080319082307/http://www.overlandclub.jp/en/info/vn_aodai.html |archivedate = 2008-03-19}}</ref>。衣服必须量体裁衣，裁缝一般要花几个星期才能完成。长袄在美国花费200美元，在越南花40美元<ref name="Bhudsabourg">{{cite web |url=http://www.nhamagazine.com/012008/feature/aodai.shtml |title=Ao Dai Couture |work=Nha magazine. |accessdate=2008-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080408004749/http://www.nhamagazine.com/012008/feature/aodai.shtml |archivedate=2008-04-08  }}</ref>。

[[德克萨斯州大学奥斯汀分校|德克萨斯州大学奥斯汀分校]]助理教授Nhi T. Lieu写道：“从象征意义上看，长袄唤起乡土性别形象所带来的怀旧和永恒，为侨居海外的越南人渴望<ref name="Lieu"/>。”她写道，穿长袄工作的困难点出衣服的脆弱和无辜<ref name="Lieu"/>。越南作家赞成将长袄作为校服，指出穿着它的不便，不失为是老师教学生谦虚、谨慎、细心等女性主义行为的好处<ref name="Leshkowich97" />。

长袄出现在以越南为主题或相关的影片中。1987年影片《[[早安越南|早安越南]]》，[[罗宾·威廉姆斯|罗宾·威廉姆斯]]所饰演的角色首次来到西贡，受到穿着长袄女性的欢迎。1992年电影《[[印度支那_(电影)|印度支那]]》和《[[情人_(1992年电影)|情人]]》启发多家国际时装公司设计长袄系列<ref name="Wakefield">{{cite web|url=http://articles.getacoder.com/Ao_Dai_-_Vietnamese_Plus_Size_Fashion_Statement_808529x1200042917.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090216234340/http://articles.getacoder.com/Ao_Dai_-_Vietnamese_Plus_Size_Fashion_Statement_808529x1200042917.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2009-02-16 |title=Ao Dai — Vietnamese Plus Size Fashion Statement |accessdate=2008-07-14 }}</ref>，包括[[普拉达|普拉达]]的SS08系列和[[乔治·阿玛尼|乔治·阿玛尼]]系列。2007年[[越南电影|越南电影]]《{{le|穿白丝绸的女人|The White Silk Dress}}》，长袄是贫穷家庭母亲留给女儿们的唯一遗产<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vietq.wordpress.com/2006/10/16/vietnam-send-ao-lua-ha-dong-to-pusan-film-festl/ |title=Vietnam send Ao Lua Ha Dong to Pusan Film Festival |work=VietNamNet Bridge |year=2006 |accessdate=2008-07-13 |archive-date=2008-05-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080507232447/http://vietq.wordpress.com/2006/10/16/vietnam-send-ao-lua-ha-dong-to-pusan-film-festl/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。目前在建的65层大楼{{le|河内乐天中心|Lotte Center Hanoi}}外观灵感出自长袄<ref>{{cite news|title="Nóc nhà" Hà Nội sẽ cao 65 tầng|author=Tuấn Cường|newspaper=[[Tuoi_Tre|Tuoi Tre]]|language=|accessdate=2009-04-26|url=http://www.tuoitre.com.vn/Tianyon/Index.aspx?ArticleID=192066&ChannelID=3|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070328173624/http://www.tuoitre.com.vn/tianyon/Index.aspx?ArticleID=192066&ChannelID=3|archive-date=2007-03-28|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。越南设计师为2008年7月越南[[芽庄市|芽庄市]][[环球小姐|环球小姐]]选美竞赛的参赛选手们设计长袄<ref>{{Cite web |title=Miss Universe contestants try on ao dai |newspaper=Vietnam.net Bridge |year=2008 |url=http://english.vietnamnet.vn/lifestyle/2008/06/789353/ |accessdate=2008-08-02 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080701025340/http://www.english.vietnamnet.vn/lifestyle/2008/06/789353/ |archivedate=2008-07-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

在越南海外，美国最大越南人社群加利福尼亚州圣何塞每年都会举办的越南长袄节<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://aodaifestival.com/ |title={{!}} A Celebration of Vietnamese Art and Culture<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2020-09-19 |archive-date=2016-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402142318/http://aodaifestival.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在节日创办人珍妮·杜的指导下，该活动成为了国际化设计师活动。

== 现代长袄 ==
数十年来，越南统一和发展的快速步伐见证着传统长袄的变更。这并不意味着传统长袄从越南人的生活中消失，相反，变得更加适应现代生活了。国家的日益发展要求变更和适应能力。传统长袄也不例外，不仅是因为它的设计不符合现代越南人的审美观点。事实上，因为传统长袄穿着在日常生活中不方便，所以一定要“现代化”。因此，长袄的设计不适合长途工作或旅行。此外，越南天气的极端也让民众对穿长袄望而却步。因此，人们从设计和材质上改造长袄，使穿着者感到更加舒服便捷<ref>{{cite web |url=https://canifa.com/blog/glossary/ao-dai-cach-tan/ |title=Áo dài cách tân |work=CANIFA Blog |year=2017 |accessdate=2017-09-26 |archive-date=2017-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926143153/https://canifa.com/blog/glossary/ao-dai-cach-tan/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。

现代长袄于数年前出现。然而，还是有人把长袄看成正式服装，如教师、空乘、接待员。直到2016年底，现代长袄衍生了数百种款式，受大众欢迎。衣领、袖子或前后摆长度有所修改。此外，现代人倾向于长袄配[[裙裤|裙裤]]和短裙，而不是配裤子。变更的不只是设计，人们还用不同的布料制作长袄，例如丝绸、锦织物或薄纱织物<ref>{{cite web |url=https://giaitri.vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/thoi-trang/bo-suu-tap/nha-thiet-ke-minh-chau-khoe-ao-dai-cach-tan-2979118.html |title=Nhà thiết kế Minh Châu khoe áo dài cách tân |work=VnExpress |year=2014 |accessdate=2014-04-17 |archive-date=2014-04-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140420052317/http://giaitri.vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/thoi-trang/bo-suu-tap/nha-thiet-ke-minh-chau-khoe-ao-dai-cach-tan-2979118.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>  。

伴随着现代长袄的浪潮，批评有所转变。希望在长袄中保留传统价值的人们认为现代长袄五花八门。越南设计师德雄先生认为：“我坚信现代长袄不属于越南。如果我们继续倡导现代长袄的潮流，传统长袄就会被埋汰......<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dantri.com.vn/van-hoa/ao-dai-cach-tan-dang-bi-pha-nat-bien-dang-2017020311095488.htm |title=Áo dài cách tân đang bị phá nát, biến dạng? |work=Dân trí |year=2017 |accessdate=2017-09-26 |archive-date=2017-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926144202/http://dantri.com.vn/van-hoa/ao-dai-cach-tan-dang-bi-pha-nat-bien-dang-2017020311095488.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>”尽管如此，越南青少年对现代长袄仍青睐有加。

